Audio/Z80/YM debug status (2025-01-25)

What changed recently
- Z80 timing fixes: EI delay, IRQ acknowledge cycles, Z80 g_clock loop fix.
- Added Z80 wait cycles for YM reads and PSG writes.
- Added Z80 banked read/write wait cycles (EUTHERDRIVE_Z80_BANK_WAIT, default 16).
- YM busy timing uses SystemCycles; headless now advances SystemCycles per frame and runs Z80 inside a Begin/EndSystemCycleSlice.
- Added YM busy emulation flag: EUTHERDRIVE_EMULATE_YM_BUSY.
- Fixed YM KEYON channel mapping to match otheremumdemu gap: {0,1,2,-1,3,4,5,-1}.
- M68K write16 to Z80 window now writes upper byte only (matches otheremumdemu behavior).

Key instrumentation added
- YM timers: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_YM_TIMER (+ limit).
- YM key on/off: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_YM_KEY (+ limit).
- YM write stats: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_YM_WRITE_STATS (+ limit).
- DAC stats: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_DAC.
- Z80 audio rate: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_Z80_AUDIO_RATE (+ every/start frame).
- Z80 bank read limit: EUTHERDRIVE_TRACE_Z80BANK_READ_LIMIT (0 = unlimited).

Findings so far
- Aladdin: DAC bank traces show Z80 PCM reads from banked 68k region around 0x1D0000, sequential reads in 0x1Fxx Z80 window. YM key on/off activity looks normal. Audio still sounds wrong (fast/backwards/incomplete), likely not just speed.
- Quackshot: YM write stats show mostly reg 0x27 writes, few key-on events; missing music suggests driver upload or Z80 mailbox handshake still suspect. Need to see Z80 window writes/MBX sync and YM writes with focused logging.

Open hypotheses
- Some games may be sensitive to how VDP/VRAM writes interact with DMA gating; check for dropped VDP writes and use VRAM range logs to confirm actual tile updates.
- For missing music: Z80 driver upload or mailbox handshakes may be partial; look for dropped writes in Z80 window or wrong word/byte write behavior.

Recent logs produced
- quackshot_audio_stats.log
- quackshot_mem_audio.log (focus: Z80WIN/MBX/YM key+write)
- aladdin_dacbank.log, aladdin_ymwrite.log, aladdin_dac_stats.log, aladdin_z80win_1fxx.log, aladdin_z80ram_1fxx.log

Notes on savestates
- Some savestates failed to load (md_vdp g_color array error); for audio issues, cold boot may be required.
